# --- Internal working documentation: the public/internal boundary ------------
# The documentation boundary is now STRUCTURAL, not suffix-guessed:
#
#   docs/*.md        -> PUBLIC curated reference (see docs/README.md).
#   docs/design/**   -> INTERNAL design notes, roadmaps, and forward-looking
#                       plans. Kept in THIS development repository for maintainers
#                       and contributors with access, but NEVER shipped in the
#                       public source archive (`git archive`, honored
#                       automatically) or the fresh public launch repository
#                       (scripts/create_public_launch_repo.sh filters the tree by
#                       these entries).
#
# This block is the single source of truth for what documentation is public vs
# internal. For any new internal doc, put it under docs/design/ (do not add
# ad-hoc top-level exclusions — top-level docs/ is the public reference surface).
#
# --- BEGIN history-scan-exempt ------------------------------------------------
# scripts/ci/check_public_history_text.sh derives its git-HISTORY scan
# exclusions ONLY from export-ignore entries between this marker and the
# matching "END history-scan-exempt" marker below (see that script's awk
# derivation) — NOT from every export-ignore line in this file.
#
# That is a deliberate, narrow decoupling (2026-07-10, CR-2 fix). export-ignore
# controls what a `git archive` / GitHub "Download ZIP" artifact or a fresh
# scripts/create_public_launch_repo.sh checkout contains. It does NOT control
# what reaches the public remote day-to-day: this repo's actual publish path is
# a direct `git push` of ordinary merged history (docs/WORKFLOW.md rule 6), so
# a tree being export-ignored from the *artifact* does not make its
# history-reachable content safe to stop content-scanning. Only docs/design/**
# and the LEGACY paths below have an explicit, written decision that their
# history is also out of this guard's scope. Any new export-ignore entry —
# including future fidelity-program paths — goes OUTSIDE this block by
# default. Moving one inside requires the same kind of explicit, written
# sign-off recorded right here, not just an incidental .gitattributes edit.
docs/design/** export-ignore
#
# LEGACY paths, retained on purpose. Internal docs previously lived at these
# paths (before consolidation under docs/design/). They match nothing in the
# current tree; kept here purely so this guard keeps ignoring historical
# internal content under these paths that is now gone from HEAD. Do not remove
# them without also updating that guard.
docs/superpowers/** export-ignore
docs/remaster-aaa/** export-ignore
docs/*_PLAN.md export-ignore
docs/*_ROADMAP.md export-ignore
docs/*_REVIEW.md export-ignore
docs/PRE_SHIP_REVIEW_*.md export-ignore
docs/*_AUDIT_*.md export-ignore
docs/*_SURVEY.md export-ignore
docs/*_WIP.md export-ignore
docs/*_STATUS.md export-ignore
docs/*_GLIDEPATH.md export-ignore
docs/*_MAP.md export-ignore
docs/*_GUIDE.md export-ignore
docs/*_THEORY.md export-ignore
# --- END history-scan-exempt --------------------------------------------------
#
# Fidelity program (2026-07-10 internal-only decision D1; see
# docs/design/FIDELITY_REVIEW_AND_PLAN_2026-07-10.md). Its tooling and working
# data live outside docs/design/, so they need their own export-ignore entries
# for the git-archive / public-launch-repo artifact, below. They are
# DELIBERATELY placed OUTSIDE the history-scan-exempt block above: these trees
# are still pushed to the public remote verbatim as ordinary history
# (docs/WORKFLOW.md rule 6), so scripts/ci/check_public_history_text.sh must
# keep content-scanning their history even though a fresh archive/launch-repo
# checkout never contains them. (An earlier version of this change listed
# these entries ahead of the LEGACY block; the guard's then-unscoped awk
# derivation picked them up automatically and silently stopped scanning their
# history — CR-2, 2026-07-10 fidelity-leak review. Do not move these back
# inside the marked block above without the same explicit sign-off it requires.)
docs/fidelity/** export-ignore
tools/fidelity/** export-ignore
baselines/tapes/** export-ignore
#
# Native-port defect audit (docs/audit/**): internal robustness/correctness
# findings (unfixed crash repros, signing-pipeline gaps, malformed-asset faults).
# A public list of unfixed defects does not belong in the release artifact, so it
# is export-ignored — but DELIBERATELY kept OUTSIDE the history-scan-exempt block
# above so its history is still content-scanned on the direct-push path.
docs/audit/** export-ignore
#
# tools/tests/test_fidelity_ledger.py lives in the general (public) tools/tests/
# directory, not under tools/fidelity/, so the glob above misses it. It exists
# solely to unit-test the internal tools/fidelity/ledger.py (imports it
# directly), so it is exactly as internal as the tree it tests. Kept OUTSIDE
# the history-scan-exempt block above, for the same direct-push reason.
tools/tests/test_fidelity_ledger.py export-ignore
